data.name: EditPeakScoringModel_ExplictPeakBoundsWarning
data.value:
Are you sure you want to train a peak scoring model for this document?
This document uses peak boundaries from spectral libraries. When these boundaries are used, Skyline does not perform its own peak detection.
Before training a peak scoring model, it is recommended that you follow these steps:
1. Navigate to "Settings > Peptide Settings - Libraries" tab and click "Edit List". 2. Select a library item, click "Edit", and uncheck the "Use explicit peak bounds" checkbox. 3. Navigate to "Edit > Manage Results" and click the "Re-score" button.
This will provide Skyline with a variety of candidate peaks to evaluate peak quality.
